---
import Badge from '@/components/Badge.astro';
import Link from '@/components/icons/Link.astro';
import Lightbox from '@/components/Lightbox.astro';
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Work - Andrew Monty">
  <main class="p-8 mx-auto">
    <article
      class="mx-auto prose prose-natural dark:prose-invert [&_img]:rounded-lg [&_img]:border-2 [&_img]:border-muted [&_img]:cursor-zoom-in [&_h2]:font-display [&_h2]:font-semibold">
      <h1 class="not-prose mb-8 text-2xl font-display dark:text-neutral-200">
        <a href="/" class="font-bold hover:underline text-muted-foreground"
          >Andrew Monty</a
        >
        <span class="font-mono text-muted">/</span>
        Work
      </h1>
      <p>
        A selection of web projects I've worked on, or am currently working on.
      </p>

      <h2>
        <a
          href="https://amplinks.app"
          class="not-prose flex items-center gap-2 hover:underline">
          amplinks.app
          <Link class="text-muted-foreground" />
        </a>
      </h2>
      SaaS to run your service business (HVAC, plumbing, electrical, etc.) Started
      by an HVAC contractor dissatisfied with other software options. I've been improving
      design, performance, and adding <a href="https://amplinks.app/changelog"
        >new features</a
      >.
      <img
        src="/assets/amplinks.app.png"
        class="mt-4"
        onclick="openLightbox('/assets/amplinks.app.png')"
      />
      <div class="flex gap-1 flex-wrap">
        <Badge>react</Badge>
        <Badge>nextjs</Badge>
        <Badge>firebase</Badge>
        <Badge>tailwind</Badge>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <h2>
        <a
          href="https://condensate.app"
          class="not-prose flex items-center gap-2 hover:underline">
          condensate.app
          <Link class="text-muted-foreground" />
        </a>
      </h2>
      <p>
        Companion app of sorts to Amplinks, experimenting with what an
        AI-assisted HVAC diagnostic app would look like.
      </p>
      <p>
        Learned a lot about programatically interacting with LLMs, nuances of
        http streaming responses, and Progressive Web App compatibility.
      </p>
      <div
        class="-mx-8 px-8 pl-18 overflow-x-auto lg:overflow-visible flex justify-evenly [&_img]:h-96 [&_img]:-ml-10 [&_img]:hover:z-10">
        <img
          src="/assets/condensate-1.png"
          onclick="openLightbox('/assets/condensate-1.png')"
        />
        <img
          src="/assets/condensate-2.png"
          onclick="openLightbox('/assets/condensate-2.png')"
          class="translate-y-3"
        />
        <img
          src="/assets/condensate-3.png"
          onclick="openLightbox('/assets/condensate-3.png')"
        />
        <img
          src="/assets/condensate-4.png"
          onclick="openLightbox('/assets/condensate-4.png')"
          class="-translate-y-3"
        />
        <img
          src="/assets/condensate-5.png"
          onclick="openLightbox('/assets/condensate-5.png')"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-1 flex-wrap">
        <Badge>php</Badge>
        <Badge>laravel</Badge>
        <Badge>livewire</Badge>
        <Badge>neuronai</Badge>
        <Badge>tailwind</Badge>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <h2>
        <a
          href="https://andrewmonty.website"
          class="not-prose flex items-center gap-2 hover:underline">
          andrewmonty.website
          <Link class="text-muted-foreground" />
        </a>
      </h2>
      <p>
        He put the name of the thing in the thing... This is the only one I can
        <a href="https://github.com/AndrewMonty/AndrewMonty.github.io">show source</a>
        for.
      </p>
      <div class="relative h-100">
        <iframe src="/" class="absolute rounded-lg border-2 border-muted transform origin-top-left scale-50 w-[200%] h-200"></iframe>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-6 flex gap-1 flex-wrap">
        <Badge>astro</Badge>
        <Badge>tailwind</Badge>
        <Badge>cloudflare pages</Badge>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <h2>
        <a
          href="https://offbeatcanine.com"
          class="not-prose flex items-center gap-2 hover:underline">
          offbeatcanine.com
          <Link class="text-muted-foreground" />
        </a>
      </h2>
      <p>
        In an industry where everyone uses the same squarespace template or
        wordpress theme, a custom website really stands out! Snappy performance,
        simple navigation, responsive design, clear and readable content have
        helped bring in a lot of new leads!
      </p>
      <img
        src="/assets/offbeatcanine.com.png"
        onclick="openLightbox('/assets/offbeatcanine.com.png')"
      />
      <div class="flex gap-1 flex-wrap">
        <Badge>astro</Badge>
        <Badge>tailwind</Badge>
        <Badge>netlify</Badge>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <h2>
        <a
          href="https://levelupcaninenh.com"
          class="not-prose flex items-center gap-2 hover:underline">
          levelupcaninenh.com
          <Link class="text-muted-foreground" />
        </a>
      </h2>
      <p>
        Blogging on a budget. A git based CMS helps this trainer manage content
        themselves, without having to write markdown, and keeping the simplicity
        of a static site.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/assets/levelupcaninenh.com.png"
        onclick="openLightbox('/assets/levelupcaninenh.com.png')"
      />
      <div class="flex gap-1 flex-wrap">
        <Badge>astro</Badge>
        <Badge>tailwind</Badge>
        <Badge>netlify</Badge>
        <Badge>pagescms</Badge>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <h2>JLE Industries</h2>
      <p>
        Sadly no longer in service, one of my last projects at JLE was putting a
        fresh coat of paint on the website ðŸ’…
      </p>
      <img
        src="/assets/jleindustries.com.png"
        onclick="openLightbox('/assets/jleindustries.com.png')"
      />
      <div class="flex gap-1 flex-wrap">
        <Badge>php</Badge>
        <Badge>laravel</Badge>
        <Badge>livewire</Badge>
        <Badge>tailwind</Badge>
        <Badge>aws</Badge>
        <Badge>mysql</Badge>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <h2>DriverOS</h2>
      <p>
        Tired of dealing with clunky old desktop software, we built a custom web
        app to interface with industry standard transportation management
        software. The timeline view was the killer feature of DriverOS, allowing
        dispatchers intuitive insight into the status of their whole fleet.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/assets/driver-os.png"
        onclick="openLightbox('/assets/driver-os.png')"
      />
      <div class="flex gap-1 flex-wrap">
        <Badge>php</Badge>
        <Badge>laravel</Badge>
        <Badge>tailwind</Badge>
        <Badge>livewire</Badge>
        <Badge>aws</Badge>
        <Badge>mysql</Badge>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <h2>
        <a
          href="https://cambridgefcu.com"
          class="not-prose flex items-center gap-2 hover:underline">
          cambridgefcu.com
          <Link class="text-muted-foreground" />
        </a>
      </h2>
      <p>
        I think this was my first freelance project, the design is a bit dated,
        but if it ain't broke, don't fix it! It's still serving the customer
        well.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/assets/cambridgefcu.com.png"
        onclick="openLightbox('/assets/cambridgefcu.com.png')"
      />
      <div class="flex gap-1 flex-wrap">
        <Badge>html</Badge>
        <Badge>css</Badge>
        <Badge>cloudcannon</Badge>
      </div>

      <hr />

      <div class="flex justify-center">
        <button
          onclick="window.scrollTo({top: 0, behavior: 'smooth'})"
          class="font-semibold hover:underline">&uarr; top</button
        >
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
  <Lightbox />
</BaseLayout>
